This program takes an array as input from user and finds out the maximum difference between any two consecutive numbers in that array. The input will be taken from standard input stream using buffer reader. After taking all inputs we need to find the maxmimum difference between any two consecutive elements in the given array. We can use the following approach to solve this problem:
      - Firstly we initialize some variables like minimum value of the array,maximum value of the array,current element's index,number of elements in the array etc.
      - Then we start iterating over each element in the array starting with second element because we want to compare current element with previous one. So we keep track of the current element's index by incrementing j variable after every iteration.
      - If the current element is less than or equal to the previous one then we update the minimum value of the array and set the flag to true so that when next time we encounter a greater number we can reset our minimum value to the current element.
      - Whenever we get a greater number in the array we check whether the difference between current element and previous element is more than the previously stored maximum difference.If yes we replace the maximum difference with the new calculated difference else we just continue to iterate over the array.
      - Finally at the end we print the maximum difference found in the array.

