#### Title:

    This program checks whether or not given string contains number "7".

    #### Description:

    The first line will be an integer N that indicates how many test cases follow. Each case consists of one line containing a single word consisting of lowercase English letters. For each case print either Yes or No on a separate line indicating whether or not the word contains the digit seven.

    #### Solution:

    In order to solve this problem we need to understand the following things about the input data:

    Firstly, there are no spaces between words so we can use Scanner method.next() which returns the next complete token from this scanner. If you want to know more about Scanners check out [this](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/java-lang-stringtokenizer-split-method/) link.

    Secondly, the length of the numbers is limited by 50 characters. So we don't have to worry about memory issues when reading strings with large lengths. We can just read them as Strings and then convert them into integers using Integer.parseInt().

    Thirdly, all inputs consist of lowercase letters. So we don't have to worry about converting uppercase letters to lowercase ones.

    Fourthly, for every case after reading the whole string we just have to check if our string contains number 7 and print appropriate message.

